//! A sub-module which declares all the first level interrupt handlers (which are in assembly), and 
//! then registeres all of them in the IDT. This is done to allow the multi-layered interrupt 
//! handling approach where any part of the OS can register handlers on the fly and without 
//! needing to use any assembly code. Please keep in mind that all the following definitions were
//! generated by a python script.
//!
//! `Author` : Ardalan Ahanchi
//! `Date` : Feb 2021

